        "committer": {
          "name": "James Nunez",
          "email": "jnunez@whamcloud.com",
          "date": "2019-11-13 18:31:52.000000000",
          "tz": -420
        },
        "subject": "LU-10553 tests: create and cleanup test specific working dir",
        "message": "LU-10553 tests: create and cleanup test specific working dir\n\nWe have seen a variety of tests fail because they are not\nto clean up a file or directory left behind by a previous\ntest suite.  We need to make and, when the test suite is\ndone, remove a specific working directory for each test\nsuite.  Thus, this can insulate each test suite from each\nother and reduce these failures.\n\nTo do this work, there is related clean up for the DIR*\nvariables that can be done:\n* sanity-flr makes use of DIR3. So, add DIR3 to assert_DIR().\n* assert_DIR() is called in run_test() and run_test() is\ncalled for every test in a test suite. This seems excessive.\nLet’s remove the call to assert_DIR() in run_test() and\nmake sure each test suite calls assert_DIR() and checks the\nreturn code.\n* assert_DIR() exits with an error code. Let’s change the\nexit() to a return() so that callers to assert_DIR() can\ncheck the return code and choose to exit or not.  We should\ncheck the return code and call error if the return code is\nnot true(0) for all scripts that use DIR*.\n* We export all the DIR* variables in sanitize_parameters()\nwhich is called in check_and_setup_lustre().  Thus, we can\nremove export of DIR2 in init_test_env().\n* Add DIR3 and MOUNT3 parameters to sanitize_parameters().\n* The MOUNTED variable is not used in check_and_setup_lustre()\nand should be removed.\n* Grab the first input parameter to check_and_cleanup_lustre()\nand, if it exists, use this as the directories to remove at\nthe end of the test suite.  If it does not exist, use the\nexisting expression “rm -rf $DIR/[Rdfs][0-9]*”.\n\nTest-Parameters: trivial\nSigned-off-by: James Nunez <jnunez@whamcloud.com>\nChange-Id: I0f28f47392a604951af4e15c4e7dd1a1fd1375eb\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
